  "doc_id": "38501",
  "text": "Direct infiltration of peripheral nerves by carcinomas is a common feature of advanced tumor progression; however, it is only rarely encountered in nerve biopsies performed in the context of peripheral neuropathy. On the other hand, diffuse infiltration of peripheral nerves by malignant lymphomas is rather common and may involve the sural nerve. Spread of the lymphoma to the peripheral nerves (neurolymphomatosis) may even occur early in the course of the disease, thus mimicking neuritis [CITATION_1] .",
